    <meta name="citation_reference" content="Devlin, J., Chang, M.-W., Lee, K. &amp; Toutanova, K. BERT: pre-training of deep bidirectional transformers for language understanding. In Proc. 2019 Conference of the North American Chapter of the Association for Computational Linguistics: Human Language Technologies (eds Burstein, J., Doran, C. &amp; Solorio, T.) 1, 4171&#8211;4186 (2019). This paper introduced masked language modelling, a widely used technique for training language models where parts of a text sequence are hidden (masked) in order for the model to fill in the blanks. This strategy can be extended beyond text to other data types."/>
